headline.main: WOMEN VOTE DOWN NEUTRALITY 4 TO 3; Two of Each Major Party in the House Back Changes -- Republicans Opposed

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 13 (AP) -- A majority of women members of the House went on record in favor of letting ships flying Old Glory sail where they please on the seven seas with cannon on their prows.
abstract: Explains vote on Neutrality Act war zone sec repeal, House
